	(text "--> A larger value resistor allows for a theoretically greater maximum current that can be sensed \n	without exceeding the current range of the unit. However, in application a larger range with \n	linear amplification will trade off resolution. Additionally, greater voltges lead to greater\n	power dissipation across the high side resistor which becomes a design and safety challenge."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 240.03 56.388 0)
		(effects
